August 17 at 1:47 PM ·

Schedule change for DCHS Football...The Decatur Central High School varsity football team will begin its season at Center Grove High School on August 21st, 2020 at 7:00 P.M. This game was previously scheduled for August 28th, 2020 at Decatur Central. We are currently working on scheduling a Week 2 opponent.

The freshman football team will start as originally scheduled, August 22nd, 2020, at New Palestine High School at 10:00 A.M. Junior Varsity will play Center Grove JV @ Decatur Central on August 22nd, 2020 at 10:00 AM.

Parent tickets will be available tomorrow. Number of tickets per player to be determined. Link for tickets will be emailed tomorrow as soon as possible.

General Admission Tickets will be available starting Wednesday.

#GoHawks

post_text:
Dear Decatur Township Families,

The survey sent out earlier was to strictly help us gather information as we work to create our re-entry plan for our students this fall. We would like to gauge the interest of our families to determine if you are interested in our remote learning option or would prefer to send your children to school. We are continuing to work out the details for both options, but are truly needing your input as we finalize details which will be shared in the upcoming weeks.

Further details will be forthcoming as we work with our Marion County Board of Health to finalize our safe school environment for this upcoming school year.
We need this completed by June 26, 2020

post_text:
Good morning!

If your child's iPad has been shut down it needs to be returned to the MSD of Decatur Township's Technology office. You can return the iPad on Tuesday or Thursday of each week at our office, 5106 South High School Road Suite #B (located near the Middle School Main Entrance) between the hours of 10am and noon until June 25th, or you can call the technology office to make other arrangements if those times will not work for you.

If your child is enrolled in summer school and your child's iPad has been disabled please contact the Technology office at 317-856-2221.

Thank you,

MSD of Decatur Technology Team

shared_text:
DCHS Live
June 11 at 5:30 PM ·

PRERECORDED GRADUATION SPEECHES

Congratulation to the Decatur Central Class of 2020.
What a crazy year! A school year cut short by Covid-19. No prom, no spring sports, no yearend goodbyes, and no traditional graduation. As always, our students adapt and go forward.

This year's graduation will be via social distancing and live-streaming. All speeches have been prerecorded to play before graduation and for families, friends and classmates to enjoy later.

Time Stamps
00:07 - Senior Leaders
00:34 - Jack Sells DCHS Salutatorian
04:22 - Destiny Fanning DTSE Salutatorian
08:17 - Riley Iaria DCHS Valedictorian
11:30 - Nate Wachnicki DCHS Valedictorian
16:08 - Jocelyn McKinney DTSE Valedictorian
19:21 - Kameron Packard DCHS & District Teacher of the Year
25:50 - Turning of the Tassels

Background Music: https://www.bensound.com

Tomorrow is the last day to do online registration for the 20 -21 school year. We will begin shutting iPads and Hotspots down starting Saturday, May 30th for those who have not registered.
For those who are not returning please bring your iPads/hotspots back on June 1st or June 2nd either at the Blue and Gold Academy ( back entrance) or DTSE (front entrance) from 9 am -1 pm and 3 pm-6 pm to avoid being charged for the iPad and Mifi.
Students returning to a Decatur School should use the returning student button on the website with the parent login. New to the district ( did not attend a Decatur School Last year )should register as a new student.
register at DecaturProud.org. If you've forgotten your log in credentials or are having trouble signing in, please contact your child's school for assistance.

Decatur Township Fire Department
May 15 at 2:18 PM ·

Decatur Fire News:

We appreciate everyone that has offered their support and words of encouragement. This week and weeks past we have had several community residents and businesses who went above and beyond by donating a meal for our crews, making cloth masks, and just checking on us to make sure we are doing okay in general.
Let us thank some of those individuals.
Businesses – Pasquale’s Pizza in Marwood, Domino’s on Mann Road, O’Charley’s in Camby.
Individuals in general Erin, Kris and Dixie Randall for the masks. Mr. & Mrs. McCoy for lunch.
Let us also remember how we are all in this together to beat this new normal. Keep social distancing, wear masks, wash your hands.

Decatur Township Drug Free Coalition
April 8 at 10:53 AM ·

Our Decatur Township community mourns the loss of a true Decatur great, Jack Butler, to the COVID 19 virus. Jack was a former teacher at West Newton Elementary School and has spent his retirement serving our community through the Decatur Township Lions Club and the Alumni Association. I have the pleasure of sharing office space with the Alumni Association and really got to know Jack much better in the past year. He is the definition of Decatur Proud!

Please join us in praying for strength and comfort now and in the days to come for Jack's family, his Lion's Club family, and our community. What a huge loss of one who served so many. 💙💛

shared_text:
Decatur Township Scholarship Association
March 21 at 10:05 PM ·

Decatur Township Scholarship Association is hoping for another successful year with our goal of providing scholarships. Even if we cannot have our Celebration, we still want to honor our donors some way and of course, the graduates of 2020 and the Decatur grads earning renewals.

Since 1992, we have awarded $1,078,550 in scholarships to our deserving students! Last year we awarded 50 scholarships. In our first year we awarded 12 scholarships. In no way could we have ever imagined this degree of success! We firmly believe our students do so well because of the support of our entire community. This year we hope that you will join us in our mission.

Please send your tax-deductible gift payable to Decatur Township Scholarship Association Inc. or DTSA at 5251 Kentucky Ave, Indpls, IN 46221 by April 5th. All donations are 501(c)(3)-tax deductible EIN# 46-3387727. 100% of your donation goes toward scholarships.

We firmly believe it takes a community to raise our Youth, and your support is a testament to that end. Thank you for making our community great.

Sincerely,
DTSA Board

post_text:
Decatur Township Families and Staff,

With the announcement of our State Governor today, I wanted to inform you that we will share a plan moving forward for our school community tomorrow, March 20, 2020. Hearing this for the first time, like many of you, we do not want to jump into a plan of action immediately today. We will plan, discuss and then share our situation and expectations to support our school community tomorrow, Friday, March 20th. That communication will be via phone, email, social media and our school websites. I want to thank all of Decatur Township for your strength and willingness to deal with this crisis head on. We will continue our mission of learning, safety, and customer service as we strive to prepare our students to be Tomorrow Ready. Thank you - as always, together, we are Decatur Proud.

Respectfully,

Dr. Prusiecki

Superintendent

Updated Technology Support Information
Posted March 16, 2020
CANVAS IS BACK UP!

This information is regarding the operation of MSD Decatur's Information Technology Department during normal operating business hours of 8am-4pm Monday through Friday.

Due to staff working from home during the Covid-19 shut down:
If you are in need of account access support for instructional platforms such as Canvas or Pearson please call 317-856-2203.

If you require support with an MSD Decatur’s Google account or the first and second-grade slide deck call 317-856-2220.

For iPad support, login and hotspot issues call 317-856-2218

For questions regarding the eLearning lessons, directions, and activities created by your teachers it is recommended to contact them directly.

For support for platforms including but not limited to MobyMax, Edulastic, Class Dojo, Seesaw, etc please contact your student’s teacher or your school office.
